{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id795a7993-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1671"},"text":"§ 1671.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Congressional statement of findings","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Congress finds that—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795a7994-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" the extension program of the Department of Agriculture and the extension activities of each State provide useful and productive educational programs for private forest and range landowners and processors and consumptive and nonconsumptive users of forest and rangeland renewable resources, and these educational programs complement research and assistance programs conducted by the Department of Agriculture;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795a7995-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" to meet national goals, it is essential that all forest and rangeland renewable resources (hereinafter in this subchapter referred to as “renewable resources”), including fish and wildlife, forage, outdoor recreation opportunities, timber, and water, be fully considered in designing educational programs for landowners, processors, and users;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795a7996-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" more efficient utilization and marketing of renewable resources extend available supplies of such resources, provide products to consumers at prices less than they would otherwise be, and promote reasonable returns on the investments of landowners, processors, and users;","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795a7997-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671/4"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"4"},"text":"(4)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" trees and forests in urban areas improve the esthetic quality, reduce noise, filter impurities from the air and add oxygen to it, save energy by moderating temperature extremes, control wind and water erosion, and provide habitat for wildlife; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id795a7998-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s1671/5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5"},"text":"(5)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" trees and shrubs used as shelterbelts protect farm lands from wind and water erosion, promote moisture accumulation in the soil, and provide habitat for wildlife.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id795a7999-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/306/s2"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–306, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/349"},"text":"92 Stat. 349","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id795a799a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id795a799b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id795a799c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective and Termination Dates","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/306/s8"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–306, § 8","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-06-30"},"text":"June 30, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/352"},"text":"92 Stat. 352","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/100/231/s2/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 100–231, § 2(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1988-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 1988","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/101/1565"},"text":"101 Stat. 1565","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/171/tVIII/s8101/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–171, title VIII, § 8101(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-05-13"},"text":"May 13, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/475"},"text":"116 Stat. 475","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/234/tVII/s7413/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–234, title VII, § 7413(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-05-22"},"text":"May 22, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1256"},"text":"110 Stat. 1256","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/246/s4/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–246, § 4(a)","children":[],"tail":", title VII, § 7413(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2008-06-18"},"text":"June 18, 2008","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/122/1664"},"text":"122 Stat. 1664","children":[],"tail":", 2017; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/113/79/tVII/s7405/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 113–79, title VII, § 7405(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2014-02-07"},"text":"Feb. 7, 2014","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/128/898"},"text":"128 Stat. 898","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/334/tVII/s7509/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–334, title VII, § 7509(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 2018","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/132/4824"},"text":"132 Stat. 4824","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/115/334/tVII/s7509/b"},"text":"“The provisions of this Act [enacting this subchapter and provision set out as a note under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1600"},"text":"section 1600 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall be effective for the period beginning "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-10-01"},"text":"October 1, 1978","children":[],"tail":", and ending "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2023-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 2023","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"shortTitle","id":"id795a799d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Short Title","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For short title of Renewable Resources Extension Act of 1978, see Short Title of 1978 Amendment note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1600"},"text":"section 1600 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
